en_701694_0	Troops of the Security Force Headquarters - Central (SFHQ-Cen) extended a warm welcome to hundreds of ‘Paada Yathra’ (foot pilgrimage) devotees when they arrived at Linthuna area in Yala on Monday (9).
en_701694_1	Troops on the directions of Major General Rukmal Dias, Commander, Security Forces - Central served refreshing drinks and bottles of water to them and inquired into their needs.
en_701694_2	Those pilgrims make their way across Yala National Park to Kathragama to attend the forthcoming Esala Festival around the end of the month of July.
en_701694_3	Under the supervision of Major General N.D Wanniarachchi, General Officer Commanding, 12 Division, troops of the 121 Brigade Headquarters supported the project.
